The paper discusses natural language question answering over knowledge graphs, which involves techniques from natural language processing, artificial intelligence, and database systems. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves structured query generation and execution, which are related to database systems, suggesting cs.DB (Databases) as another likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval and machine learning, which are related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), respectively, making them less likely but still plausible sub-categories.
